<%- include("../partials/head", { title }) %>

<section class="card proper-case">
  <p class="est">legal</p>
  <h1 class="h1">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="muted" style="margin-top: 0.35rem; font-size: 0.85rem">Last updated: 04-12-26</p>

  <div class="stack-section" style="margin-top: 1.5rem">

    <div class="stack-item">
      <h3>Overview</h3>
      <p>circle! e-friend finder collects only the data necessary to operate the platform. We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to any third party. This policy explains what we collect, how we use it, and what rights you have over your data.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stack-item">
      <h3>Information We Collect</h3>
      <p>When you sign in via osu! OAuth, we receive your public osu! profile information (including your user ID, username, avatar, global rank, badge count, and country). We also store any profile details you voluntarily provide on this site (age, gender, bio, discord username) as well as messages you send to other users and your browse filter preferences.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stack-item">
      <h3>How We Use Your Information</h3>
      <p>Your data is used to display your profile to other users, power the browse and messaging features, and allow admins to moderate the platform. We do not use your data for advertising, analytics resale, or any purpose beyond operating this service.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stack-item">
      <h3>Data Storage and Security</h3>
      <p>All user data is stored in Firebase, a Google Cloud service. Session data is stored server-side. We never store your osu! password (authentication is handled entirely through osu!'s official OAuth flow). While we take reasonable precautions, no system is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security of your data.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stack-item">
      <h3>Visibility of Your Data</h3>
      <p>Your profile (avatar, username, rank, age, gender, bio) is visible to all logged-in users on the browse page. Messages are private between you and the recipient. We do not make your email or osu! OAuth token visible to anyone.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stack-item">
      <h3>Message Monitoring and Reports</h3>
      <p>Messages are not actively monitored in real time. However, we reserve the right to review message content for moderation and safety purposes. If a user submits a report, the messages associated with or related to that report may be read by site administrators as part of the review process. By using the messaging feature, you acknowledge that your messages are not guaranteed to be private from site staff.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stack-item">
      <h3>Deleting Your Data</h3>
      <p>You can permanently delete your account at any time from the preferences page. This removes your profile, bio, preferences, and inbox from our system. Some residual data such as moderation records or reports may be retained for a short period for safety purposes.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stack-item">
      <h3>Cookies</h3>
      <p>We use a single session cookie to keep you logged in. We do not use third-party tracking cookies, advertising cookies, or any form of cross-site tracking.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stack-item">
      <h3>Children's Privacy</h3>
      <p>This site is strictly 18+. We do not knowingly collect or retain data from anyone under the age of 18. If we become aware that a minor has created an account, we will immediately terminate it and remove associated data.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<%- include("../partials/foot") %>
